caption: I'm giving this review because I miss this place so much. I come here every time I visit new orleans. The music and drinks are always excellent. The bar tenders always make me feel like a local. I literally CANNOT wait until they reopen. There is not a cooler jazz bar in new orleans.
Very nice place to have a meal. Service was good, the atmosphere is a bit too loud and boisterous for a quiet romantic meal, but overall nice spot to enjoy well prepared food.

(Translated by Google) The drinks are very good, they are wonderful, they have cocktail drinks that are very good, I can have a good time any day I go as it is an excellent place, to spend a good night too good everything and very clean  (Original) Esta muy buenas las bebidas , son maravillosas, tiene las bebidas de cocteleria que son muy buenas , me la puedo pasar muy bien cualquier dia que vaya ya que es un lugar excelente, para pasar una buena noche demasiado bueno todo y muy limpio
Probably the best cocktails I've ever had.
A relaxing place to have an after-dinner drink and enjoy the music provided.

Relaxed vibe, excellent cocktails, and wonderful service. Eric at the bar is super personable! Food is tasty & the happy hour is unbeatable. Best spot off bourbon to get away from the noise & dive bar scene
The music has changed drastically which isnt a good thing. BRING BACK JAZZ. The staff are still amazing though and they make amazing drinks. Food is great as well.
Low-key one of the best bars in the French quarter. Excellent cocktails, excellent food, great space. Tucked away in a quiet corner away from the craziness surrounding it.

Awesome spot just off of Bourbon st.  We had a birthday party there and the staff and management went well above and beyond in making sure our party went off without a hitch.  We were given a private room with champagne and drinks already at the table awaiting our arrival.  The drinks were never empty but the plates were! Both the food and the drinks are top notch!  Highly highly recommend The Bombay Club for anything from a quick drink to a full out party.  11/10.
Great atmosphere and happy hour. They even had a jazz pianist the started around 9pm!!! 🥰🥰🥰 Food and drinks were all delicious. I'll definitely return.

Was recommended by a family member. They will definitely be receiving a Christmas gift this year. Had a large group, so we were able to try a good portion of the menu. The food was amazing and varied. The drinks were deliciousness ( I recommend "Meet your Maker") and strong. And the atmosphere is very perfect for a relaxed night out. Check this place out anytime your in NOLA
One of favorite places in NOLA! Got married in their courtyard!

The cocktails are delicious and the decor delightful but here’s the misstep. They took food off the happy hour menu.  To the AGM,  Please make these necessary amendments to your website so patrons are aware. I showed up at 6:30pm on a Wednesday night expecting to be served food and drink during the happy hour as currently advertised. However, I was only offered the drinks happy hour menu. I requested the food happy hour menu and was told it wasn't on offer.  P.S. You don't have enough options for small bites on your regular menu. Please take this feedback under advisement. :)
Very Nice Place with Awesome Cocktails

Came here on a Monday night.  The bar was fairly empty.  We ordered two drinks from the bartender.  I didn't like my drink, so I just sipped from my husband's.  The bartender pressed me to order something else, insisting if I didn't like the drink, he could make me anything else.  At first I said no, since I hadn't planned on even finishing a whole cocktail, wanting more to just try the place.  But I finally agreed to another cocktail.   When we asked for the bill from the bartender, it was for the price of three cocktails!   We had not even finished one of the cocktails, and now paid for three.

Enjoyed our time at the Bombay Club last night. Had the the crab beignets  and the bread pudding for dessert. Both delicious! Enjoyed my first Vieux Carré. The music was great as was our server Ashlee. We will be back!
Expensive and full of tourists.  Booths with curtains make it good for more private times.
Beautiful atmosphere, music, stuff, drinks and food
Great hand crafted drinks
Great music, good.prices for the area. Friendly attentive staff.
I had the best gator sausage here. Check it out. The vibe is very chill as well. Piano bar
Bad service. Bait & switch  happy hour specials. Sad & disappointing.

Where to begin with this hidden gem. The service was great, the food was excellent, and the drinks were impeccable. I had the short rib grilled cheese and it was divine. The Bombay Club martini and the vieux carre were two of the best drinks I've yet had in New Orleans. My friend ordered a veggie flat bread which we loved. The atmosphere was cozy and warm with book shelf lined walls and an ivy covered courtyard. When I come back to New Orleans, this is a place I know I will visit again.

The Bombay Club has an intimate, tucked-away feel to it, with its out-of-the-way setting, low lights, and jazz trio. The staff are attentive and knowledgeable. Their extensive, widely varied cocktail and spirits pair well with the menu items. Mood, music, atmosphere, flavor, service—it’s all done well here. I have a new NOLA favorite!

We loved this place!  We discovered it just strolling down Conti, only a couple of blocks from our own hotel and sauntered in.    Very pretty, sedate-looking room, beautifully appointed, friendly and very professional staff, gorgeous glassware, superbly crafted cocktails, excellent prices, a terrific experience all the way around!
Got a table reservation on short notice on a busy weekend, short menu but unusual tasty dishes!
Nice ambiance, good drinks and good apps. It's a good place for escaping the rowdiness of Bourbon Street while still enjoying jazz and drinks.
tiki madness
Best shrimp and grits i've ever had. Food is on point...
Wonderful small bar with great live music and an excellent cocktail menu. Great service as well.
Enjoyed a few drinks and live music during our visit to nola.. felt like I was home in my small town.. intimate describes the setting perfectly. which was exactly what we had been looking for ..
Great place, good, ambiance, and attention. I went with my family for Thanksgiving. We had a good time.

Spent NYE here. The Music was so good they had a live Jazz band so it was more low key. The drinks were all great and not too expensive for the more price conscious. The food was also really good we got almost all the different bites this place had and enjoyed them all. Portions where a little small but we had a large group and nobody left hungry.  If you are looking for a more low key place near all the night life I would Highly suggest this place.
Rude staff. Rushed us out.
Good atmosphere. Two of us ordered a few plates to share for dinner. Not too noisy, perfect!

In previous years I've given this place a glowing review. However, they seemed to have reduced their menu size and food quality in lock step. The staff and overall dining experience is still above average but no where near what I would expect from the price or previous years I've been here.

Super disappointed after friends had been talking this place up for months (they’d visited many times in years past). Zero vegetarian options aside from the Caesar salad, which I ordered, then promptly had to send back as there was so little in the bowl, I could see the bottom of it. The server brought it back with a bit more salad in it, but after two bites I couldn’t continue to eat it. The croutons were stale, lettuce was wilted, and almost no dressing on it. To be fair, they did have a Vegetable Flatbread on the menu, but were apparently out of flatbread. Our service was extremely slow, we were there for 2.5 hours, with only having received one round of drinks and our meals (desserts were in the plans, but we decided not get any because we had been there so long already). My cocktail was also disappointing, not at all what I expected in a Sazerac. Last but not least, the women’s restroom was out of toilet paper.
Very chill atmosphere, the bartenders are super friendly.
The drinks were good nice and strong

I come to New Orleans a few times a year and would always visit the Bombay Club specifically to hear the great jazz bands they had there and to enjoy a cocktail. On my last trip I was disappointed to find on their website that none of the musicians that I used to see were there anymore and later found out the company that now owns the bar changed the music. I gave them the benefit of the doubt and still went to check it out. The entertainment was awful. There are plenty of better cocktails bars in New Orleans that I will now be going to instead.
Very nice bar! Great atmosphere!

If you're staying at the Prince Conti you have no excuse not to go here; if you're staying elsewhere you still have no excuse. This place feels like the psychic equivalent of a lambswool glove. Tip top happy hour, occasional live piano music (of the sultry cocktail bar genre) and a great spirits selection.
Old world, classic mahogany wood. Very high whiskey and bourbons
We like the music, the atmosphere, and particularly the French 75.

We came with a group of 5, the place looked good nice and comfortable seats. There was live music I enjoyed that. I ordered a pasta with shrimps but it wasn't seasoned. Not enough pasta sauce so very dry. My man and brothers chosen the lamb, and it was also very dry and overcooked. The staff was nice but she forgot alot. We were  disappointed and didn't wanted to try the cocktails no more.
Best Caesar salad ever!  Great service and friendly staff!!
Cool courtyard but a bit expensive!

One of the best cocktail bars I have ever been to. Upscale,  Cocktails are amazing here!  Live music performance is sooo good. Go there! it will get you in the mood to drink and sing! Also, it's a very good alternative to Bourbon St bars for the ones who do not want to deal with the crowd and chaos of it.
Get the biscuits. Trust me. Seriously.

My husband and I came here on a Friday night to have drinks and listen to the pianist. Loved it! Friendly and chill service, reasonable wine and cocktail selection/price. Sophisticated vibe. We went back on Saturday for more and have verbally recommended it as well.
Great place!
Drinks fantastic, food ok
Knowledgeable & friendly staff. Best Pimm's Cup in the Quarter.

If you go down to the French Quarter Bombay Club is definitely one place you would need to stop for drinks and an appetizer they most definitely specialize in craft cocktails and knowledge about the French Quarter places to visit places not to definitely going back
Blah food for the price.
Friendly staff, delicious happy hour fare. Best kept secret less than a block off of Bourbon Street.
Limited dinner menu but wonderful staff and food was good
Great martinis!😸
The happy hour here might be the best in the city, plus it’s an oasis from the insane crowds around the corner
The happy hour here is very nicely priced, food was decent and the wait staff fairly attentive.
Exceptional food, staff, atmosphere.
Our server (Ashley) was phenomenal. The fried brussel sprouts were tops. I totally recommend stopping in for dinner and cocktails
Enjoyed this place, Anna took great care of us.
Great staff and amazing food
Eric Meyer is the best barman I know and I travel a lot
Food was great, Diffently recommend the Short Rib,best I have ever had.
Amazing happy hour! Drinks were to die for and bar snacks were delicious. Great ambience and 1930s music playing to set the mood
Great date place
Great atmosphere
Hard to find.  Great atmosphere.  Solid happy hour martini.
Best secret in NOLA
Great atmosphere here in this bar just off of Bourbon. Jazz music and an excellent selection of adult beverages. They have a small courtyard as well. Food is delicious. We highly recommend.
Good drinks. Great food! Loved the relaxed atmosphere and the servers and bartenders.
GREAT service!
Classy place with great food.

Came here for an after dinner cocktail. Very pleased with the drink selection, attentive bar tenders, local musicians and comfortable seating. Nice ambience and strong cocktails. A great spot for an evening. Didn’t eat any food.
Super high-end cocktails!!!

Great food and staff, Mathew took good care of our Cendien staff. He was very attentive and made everyone feel right at home. Would reccomend 10/10. Really liked the food, and was hidden away from the beaten path so was not crowded (like everything else around here). A hidden gem.
Love happy hour! Great drinks, great food, great service!
One of my favorite bars in NOLA
Put this on your list. This bar is AMAZING! The drinks, music, and ambiance are perfection.
Love the vibe.  Cool bar to chill at
A wonderful dim and intimate location. Great quality music and fantastic cocktails. The list is HUGE!  A must visit location.

I had dinner reservations for 7pm on a Friday.  I was seated and greeted promptly. This place was Great. The atmosphere was relaxing and calming... like a cozy den.  The lights are dimmed down for a regal-sophisticated-romantic mood. This place would be great for getting together for hors d'oeuvres and lots of stiff drinks!!

Brought a large group of friends and we were very disappointed. Slow service. Missed an order and some were through eating before all were served. They were busy but very slow. Took almost an hour to get drinks started.

Online and in-person menu do not match. Discovered this through a bartender who didn't bother to face me to give the update, and after much driving to find parking and walking passed piss and filth from the streets. Didn't stay to eat. Will not return or recommend.
Love the atmosphere

Some food was good, like the scotch egg.  And dinner service was really good from a very nice server (bar service not so good, asked for lemon twists in our martinis and got olives).  But since ⅔ of us got the "fish and chips" it was the big disappointment of the evening.  Batter was chewy and oily and slipped off the fish -- not a good experience, especially for a restaurant in a city that's known for its ability to fry seafood.  Also, the croutons on our Caesar salads were stale.  This place is NOT inexpensive and can get very expensive, so these things matter a lot.  Come to think of it, never had an experience like this at Bombay Club before the Creole Cuisine Concepts restaurant chain took it over.
Fabulous JAZZ band, great food
Best drinks in town.  Hands down.  The bartenders are awesome and the prices are reasonable.
Nice music and excellent drinks!!!
Ask for Eddie, the best barber in the whole metro.

This was hands down one of the best restaurant experiences I’ve had in while. On a packed night, we were greeted multiple times, got seated and had an amazing dinner. We’ve got Crab Beignets, Mussels and Brussel Sprouts to share. Everything tasted perfect, and the server checked on us multiple time. Very romantic place with live jazz and a great customer
The service was excellent, Ashley is an amazing waitress. The food was delicious and the solo piano was perfect, we were able to listen to the music and talk and listen to each other at our table.
The food is great! ..
Lowkey and intimate bar. Good cocktails. Decent cigars. Hidden courtyard is the best feature and the live jazz.
Awesome cocktails and live jazz every night. Above average food.

Searching for late night bites and live music? Look no further. A hidden gem just off the main entrance of the Prince Conti Hotel. We were lucky enough to be seated near the jazz pianist with an outstanding view of the courtyard. Wanting to keep a birthday celebration going, we opted for the chocolate gateau with a surprising scoop of vanilla, apple pie a la mode, an Irish Coffee and chocolate martini. The drink menu is well versed and learned a thing or two about original barware shapes. Highly recommended.
Always good

Loved the place the first night I tried it, hated it the second night when I brought a group it was a complete disaster.  I had the cheeseburger the first night and the beef rib ends the second night.  The food was very good. The service was excellent on the first night, absolutely horrible the second night.  The waitresses apologized for the delay of over an hour to get our food, she said that there was a mix up in the kitchen and would bring us some bread to help while they recooked our meal...and said the manager would be over to apologize... Neither happened.  I was both disappointed and very embarrassed as I convinced our group to change reservations from another place to The Bombay Club.  Not only do I not recommend them, I encourage you to go elsewhere.
Food was great, love the atmosphere. Radiya was a fantastic server. Made us feel very taken care of on a special occasion!
Great food and service.
Fabulous cocktail menu and lovely piano!
Very classy, smooth music
Not good with new management

Oh dear, we tried to escape the tourist center. Super nice atmosphere, good drinks and literally terrible food. The chef seems to have been given a fryolator for his birthday and obviously loves it too much. Some of the food was under cook, the rest cooked to death. The famous fish&chips turned out to be a game of  "hunt the fish" amount the quarter inch thick batter that was cooked to a dark brown dust dry state. Sad!
Just ok. We thought there would be music, but never happened. Drinks are quite expensive.
A fantastic night for dinner! The staff was amazing,very accommodating! We had to change our reservation and they were totally fine about it. Great setting , authentic live jazz! Perfect!
Drinks were great...appitizers not so great. Limited menu
They didn't have live music while we were there even though they're yelp profile says music is live from 9-11 pm. We got there at 9:45 pm. Other than that ambiance is great and food is awesome
Awesome happy hour food, drinks, and an A+ bourbon selection with great prices
Always a great Martini. Dark and comfortable place . Great to bring a date

Great spot for music and cocktails. The drinks are unbeatable. I had the rattlesnake and it’s like a really tasty whisky sour. Service is fantastic too. We had Nate as our server and boy did he give good recommendations. Food was good too. Great hidden gem.
A wonderful Happy Hour, great bar with a wonderful staff.
Great dinner and outdoor courtyard.
Ok but looks better on the website.
Nice quiet respite from Bourbon.  Dark, excellent service and solid prices.

Fantastic cocktails! You won't regret visiting this place. I had: French 75, 73 and sunny, Mint Julep, and the Absinthe. All had top notch presentations; very classy.  The food selections limited but everything is good and high quality. Don't miss out; add this to your itinerary :-).
A "secret", gem in new Orleans. Great food and great music and atmosphere. Slightly slow service for our group, drinks is came after the food.
Hidden gem in an a place with overwhelming possibilities of great places to drink and eat.
A quiet bar in New Orleans!! Nice piano player and great courtyard for cigars. The only problem is they close early if they want. Very annoying
We went here because of the advertised happy hour. It was great. Small plates were enough for us to share and tasted awesome. Server had great suggestions and was a good time. Definitely going back!
This place was really nice and the food was great! Music was great and our server was super nice and helpful. I'd like to go back again whenever I visit new Orleans again.
Completely ignored by staff? What a joke. And I actually use to love that place when it was fully staffed!
Amazing food, music, and ambience!
The fish and chips are awesome
Fancy and stylish. Live music frequently but not the best acoustics. So people keep having their conversation and don't pay attention to the music enough, if you ask me.
Awesome place! Wonderful music and atmosphere... we loved it this place. We came here twice to listen to a jazz!!
Very inventive cocktails, knowledgeable and friendly staff
Quaint and elegant
Outstanding drinks, wonderful mixologists, great food!
Lovely
Bottomless mimosas and great gumbo
Beautiful ambiance, delicious and original dishes, super nice server.
Good happy hour deals

Such a nice getaway from the madness of Bourbon!  My boyfriend and i went to Arnaud’s and were recommended this after dinner. We didn’t know what it would be like, but loved our bus boy so we trusted him. We ended up at Bombay and it was amazing. The ambiance was great with refined jazz playing in the background and our bartender basically nailed our drinks on the head by simply telling him what we liked (his name is Austin). Jeremy and Kyle were great as well. Austin was not only friendly, but helped us find another bar.  Would definitely come again - such a nice place away from the craziness that can be Bourbon.
Servers gave great recommendations and all the food was delicious
Great cocktails and setting. Live music at night.

Highly recommend the brunch. We went for Easter knowing it would probably be a less crowded option since it is mostly known as a martini bar. The food was excellent and we very much enjoyed the bottomless mimosas and rose. The ambience is very cool, and, although I have not been in the evening, I imagine it is an excellent place for cocktails.
Excelent!!!
(Translated by Google) The best of jazz in New Orleans  (Original) Lo mejor del jazz en New Orleans
Great place to meet friends for drinks and socialize , good happy hour too... oh and the staff is great and friendly...
We were in New Orleans for French Quarter Fest.  We hit the Bombay Club every night for Dark Rum Old Fashions made by the best bartender in the Quarter, Kyle. Can't wait to go back.
Nice appetizers. Happy hour has a nice selection
Great after party place for drinks

Off the main drag in a quiet corner, this place has a much more laid back, almost genteel feel with a more subdued vibe and great music.  An older crowd with what appeared to be regulars... Highly recommend.
Great cocktails and staff. I pulled the super annoying "you pick my cocktail" move and (I believe her name was Antonia) the server definitely delivered!  A great, low key start to FQF2019
Hidden gem, bartenders are amazing and the jazz is perfect for this size club. Very cozy, yet a lot of fun.

What a lovely, out of the way place to spend happy hour! Just a few steps off Bourbon Street, it felt like we walked into a calm, cool oasis. We both enjoyed old-style whiskey sours garnished with luxardo cherries.
The food was great! Awesome service and really fun live Jazz!!!
Love it!!!
Good happy hour, great ambience. Fun place.

Refined civility. Folks were very attentive, and it was a very laid-back atmosphere.  The bourbon selection was very impressive. You're also able to smoke a cigar in the courtyard. Cigars came from the local cigar factory and were very good.  This is a very classy place in quite location. They make it easy to relax.  It was a great way to start the afternoon.
Great service, better atmosphere.
Great brunch specials.
Scotch egg has changed to some mostly sausage ball with a egg in it. Was way better years before they broke the recipe.
What an outstanding speakeasy with fantastic cocktails a great atmosphere and even better live music

The vibe was AMAZING!! Cozy with live jazz music and we had our own private table tucked into the wall! The food was disappointing and felt like the creations were trying to hard mixing things that maybe shouldn't go together for every dish we had. Our server was a little rude too.
Wonderful atmosphere, delicious cocktails and desserts, piano is on point. This place is a perfect classy respite from the sleaziness of Bourbon Street.
Great spot tucked away off of Bourbon Street. We were there for happy hour and the appetizers and drinks were great.

Classy joint - happy hour is a hidden gem of New Orleans. I’m glad I was a little dressed up since I would have felt out of place in jeans.  Drinks were awesome, even more so considering price for a martini during happy hour. Bartender was a true bartender and didn’t just mix well drinks.  We also ordered some $5 small bites - pretzel was delicious and melted in your mouth, beer cheese with it was a little runny but still good. Pork Rangoon was very flavorful - highly recommend.  Great ambiance and vibe, great cocktails. I was very surprised that it wasn’t completely packed.
Service was great wasn't wild about my eggs Benedict. The rest of the food was great.
Hidden little bar with a great happy hour. We loved how quiet this place was. The bartenders took time to talk to you and they also had some great recommendations.
Good vibe older crowd great coctail menu
Great food and service. Pianist was not too shabby either. Very lovely atmosphere.
Always a great experience here! Knowledgeable bartenders,  willing to give you a history lesson if you want one or just happy to let you enjoy the ambiance in a classy setting
What a gem of a Happy Hour. Love this place. Like an old mahogany library. Great service. Tricky to find. Off the hotel driveway.
So nice. Great music.

Good food and good drink prices at Happy hour. Dinner portions not large, but delicious!  Shrimp with Grits was outstanding!  Good service and an upscale setting. On a side street off of Bourbon, and that was a good thing. Sometimes the noise and drama of Bourbon street is too much.
King cake was horrendous, I get they were putting a spin on it but it was just gross. Not a fan of their grits at all. The beignets were good which is why I gave two stars.

Fantastically cozy little spot. Great live musicians. Friendly and attentive staff. During the right whether the small courtyard on the back is a nice intimate private setting for conversations. Vernis centrally-located to anywhere else in the French quarter. Nice selections of bourbon whiskeys and scotches. Very proficient bartenders at making mixed drinks.
Great cocktails and food! Try the brussel sprouts!

The service was absolutely fantastic and the General manager even come up to my table and introduced himself and left his card I went for drinks and dessert with my date for the night and it was such a good time I highly recommend this restaurant I will absolutely return next time I’m in New Orleans
Crawfish etouffee was cold and a little thin.
Good food LOUSY SERVICE!!!
Great trumpeter Leroy Jones!
A nice drink list and great atmosphere
Choices limited and music was not what I was expecting
Great food, drinks and service. Not a great selection of desserts.
Great place!
Skip the food and go here for drinks. Vast cocktail list, old time classic, and new age twists. Can rack up quite a tab at this spot
Happy hour good bites, great bartender.
Would easily be mistaken for a bar from a James Bond movie.
#1 Favorite in FQ  Nola  great everything. bartenders make u feel welcome!
Had brunch with bottomless sparkling rose. Food lovely, surroundings nice. Quite quiet when we went, felt like a bit of a hidden gem if you want a relaxed, low key meal.
(Translated by Google) Good cocktails I advise happy hour  (Original) Cocteles buenos. Aconsejo happy hour
Great food and great staff

If you're looking to get seated by a rude inattentive hostess who I believe is now serving, and then get served by a rude disrespectful uncaring server then this is the place for you! How do you mess up a gin and tonic and an old fashioned. Well you don't add the tonic and you don't put bitters in the old fashioned. This wasn't the bartenders fault as when we brought it up he admitted that he rang it in incorrectly. Even worse the server had a trainee and when he greeted the table he didn't even know his trainees name. We complained to management and they did nothing. There was one hostess that was nice though who was kinda short with longer blondish hair, but otherwise this place fails in the customer service department.
Chris and his staff do an outstanding job!!!!!
Great music, great food, great cocktails.
Excellent meal.
Great food located right off of Bourbon. Their $10 bottomless Mimosas is a great way to start the day!
Great food and service

Chalking up this not-great dining experience to the fact that it was Christmas night. Partook of the Reveillon dinner. Kitchen was out of bisque at our 8:00pm reservation and replaced with gumbo. I sent back my entree because it was far overcooked. The other entree wasn't great and the lamb lollipops were bordering on over-done. Highlight was egg nog creme brulee and cocktails. Lowlight was food mentioned above and another couple who was very dissatisfied with their meal and talked to multiple staff outlining their complaints again and again and again. Should have ordered off the regular menu. Walking in I thought it was going to be one of the best meals of 2018. Was disappointed.
My honey chose this as a dinner & a show option, both were delivered with graceful sophistication, and cocktail menu is outstanding.

The restaurant is beautiful and there was a very skilled jazz band. The bartender was funny, charming and knowledgeable, she was just incredible. We ordered food and waited for about 40 to fifty minutes. This wait went unaddressed until we mentioned it. The bartender sent a server back to the kitchen then when they didn't return with an update she went back to get an update for herself.  Once they realized how long the wait actually was the manager came out and informed us that the kitchen staff was "distracted". During this time the soda gun also malfunctioned and sprayed me with water.  About fifteen to twenty more minutes went by and the manager came back with one of the two plates we ordered saying they over cooked the chicken and had to remake it. That first dish was salty but we were starving at this point so we accepted the apology and ate it.  They "comp'd" us 2 free cocktails which was cool but only one of us was drinking. By the time the chicken, that was previously over cooked, came out I was ready to eat. Unfortunately, the chicken had ingredients, that were not mentioned on the menu, that I could not eat and I had to send it back.  Twenty more minutes later they apologized that remaking the food was taking so long. I asked them to cancel the plate because I couldn't give them any more of my time and we parted ways, forever, hopefully.

Swanky spot. Visited on Dec 30th.   Hostess was not very helpful in finding a table for 6...despite there being a ton of seats.  I have a feeling about why that happened but, moving on.  Luckily we walked in anyway and easily found a table for ourselves.  Waiter was amazing and very attentive.  He had great recommendations! Live Music was awesome. Drinks were insane.   Fresh mint and blueberries YUM.  I'll be back

$6 Churchill martinis at happy hour make this an easy choice. Also, they do a Scotch egg wrapped with Louisiana boudin sausage. Attentive and professional staff. So, there are plenty of reasons to duck into this hidden Quarter gem.
Great speakeasy. Great variety of cocktails. Upscale place.
An intimate throwback to a time of cigars and Wood lined book shelves. Great cocktails and wonderful food.

The food here is some of the best in the city! My boyfriend and I are huge foodies so we ordered up! We had boudin scotch egg, crab and chorizo beignets, cheeseburger and fries, steamed mussels and shrimp and grits.... every single very single dish was amazingly delicious! The bartenders also made us the best cocktails as well. The jazz was mellow and the ambiance was relaxed. Definitely will be back!
We loved the place! Nice music (not too loud for once), good food and dim atmosphere to relax after a crazy day in New Orleans.
Love this place! Amazing food, drinks and atmosphere. This is our new favorite New Orleans spot!
Food cold....overcooked...very disappointed.  No one to oversee.. .orders came out wrong
Fantasic food and wonderful service!
great venue. fun but not over the top

The atmosphere and the live music is great. The food was decent, a bit on the greasy side even for NO standards. Unfortunately the biggest disappointment was the cocktails. They make a big deal out of their cocktail menu but unfortunately many of them are light on alcohol and way too sweet.
Excellent ambiance, great service and creative cocktails
Lovely atmosphere. Good quiet jazz for conversations, great bar service. A little hard to find but glad we did.
Excellent music and food
Wonderful hideaway off Conti. Music volume is such that u can talk! Lovely menu. A peaceful Oasis off Bourbon Street.
#martinibar #martini #livemusic #greatfood #greatservice #frenchquarter #hiddengem
Love the atmosphere. Great mixologist
We have been visiting New Orleans for years - first visit at Bombay Club.  Service, drinks, food & atmosphere were all wonderful!

Out of all the Jazz venues in the area, this one was pre selected by my wife for my 50th birthday visit from Florida,  The selection was made based on the jazz artist who was scheduled to perform that evening . After spending over $100 bucks on food and drinks,  they tell us the jazz band won't be playing. Which in my opinion,  they probably knew that when the reservation was made. We were very disappointed. You figure they would offer some sort of compensation,  NOPE. just a non sympathetic apology.
Great bar staff and friendly atmosphere
Food is yummy, happy hour is great, service was top notch.
Nice bar, really nice staff, good drinks, lousy selection of beer

This place is incredible. A must-go while in New Orleans, especially if you love live jazz music. The appetizers, entrees, and desserts are all incredible: in my party of 7, every single person loved their food. We tried the hangar steak, the pasta with shrimp added, the market fish, and the shortrip. All delicious! The restaurant also has a great ambiance and terrific service. Our server, Nate, made excellent drink recommendations based on each of our tastes. We all loved the cocktails we received. He provided some of the best service I’ve had at any restaurant. We ordered the bottomless Mimosas and Rose' and never had a problem getting a refill. Now on to the food. I ordered the Beer Battered Crab & Chorizo Beignets and Buttermilk Fried Chicken Sandwich. The beignets were awesome! The chicken sandwich left some things to be desired. The chicken breast was too small for the bun. I couldn't taste the pimento cheese or pork belly and it was borderline dry. It was supposed to come with sweet potato chips, but I somehow ended up with lukewarm fries. I would go again because based on other reviews I've seen, I have a feeling that dinner would be better.

Well, this is one of my favorite evening places in New Orleans.  Old School, white glove, impecable tuxedoed service.  Low ceilings, dark mahogany paneling and a lot of Old English Hunt Club nostalgia.  Enjoy a Sazerac on the Chesterfield leather sofa while enjoying the nightly cabaret style entertainment.  For dinner, everything is delicious.  I've never had a mediocre meal here and always leave with a warm, fuzzy, cozy, been-cared-for feeling.  If you're staying in the adjacent Prince Conti hotel as we often do, so much the better - easy commute back to your room.
